<p>I hope these shed some light on how natural foods contain considerably less sugar than anything processed and packaged when you consider the satiating and nutritional quality. Comparing the natural sugars present in fruits or vegetables to processed sweeteners isn't a fair comparison as natural foods always have fiber and other useful nutritive enzymes, phytonutrients, vitamins, minerals and contribute to your health. Strictly speaking, the RDV is for <em>added sugar</em>, aka processed sweeteners, so it's not even relevant to fructose naturally found in fruit.</p>

<h3 id="rdv">About our Recommended Daily Value (RDV)</h3>
<p>Our tables calculating the % of RDV are based on a maximum of 36g per man and 24g per woman. These numbers are in accordance with the AMA, AHA, and CDC for <em>added sugars</em>.</p>

